  <h1>Phase 5 — Project Demonstration & Documentation</h1>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Final Demo Walkthrough</h2>
    <p>The final demo showcases the <span class="highlight">Blogging Platform</span> in action — covering post creation, editing, commenting, and real-time updates. It demonstrates user authentication and secure data handling between frontend and backend.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Project Report</h2>
    <p>The project report details the complete development lifecycle, tech stack, and architectural design. The application uses:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Frontend:</b> React.js, HTML, CSS, JavaScript</li>
      <li><b>Backend:</b> Node.js, Express.js</li>
      <li><b>Database:</b> MongoDB Atlas</li>
      <li><b>Hosting:</b> Vercel / Netlify</li>
      <li><b>Version Control:</b> GitHub</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Screenshots / API Documentation</h2>
    <p>Includes detailed screenshots for each module and REST API documentation using Swagger or Postman:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>POST /api/auth/login</code> – User Authentication</li>
      <li><code>GET /api/posts</code> – Fetch All Blog Posts</li>
      <li><code>POST /api/posts</code> – Create a New Blog Post</li>
      <li><code>PUT /api/posts/:id</code> – Edit an Existing Blog Post</li>
      <li><code>DELETE /api/posts/:id</code> – Delete a Blog Post</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Challenges & Solutions</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><b>Challenge:</b> Managing complex state across pages. <b>Solution:</b> Implemented Redux for state management.</li>
      <li><b>Challenge:</b> Secure user authentication. <b>Solution:</b> Used JWT tokens and bcrypt encryption.</li>
      <li><b>Challenge:</b> Responsive design issues. <b>Solution:</b> Applied CSS Flexbox and Grid layout.</li>
      <li><b>Challenge:</b> Slow API response. <b>Solution:</b> Optimized queries and caching mechanisms.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>GitHub README & Setup Guide</h2>
    <p>README includes instructions for setup and contribution:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Clone repo → <code>git clone https://github.com/yourusername/blogging-platform</code></li>
      <li>Install dependencies → <code>npm install</code></li>
      <li>Set up <code>.env</code> file for MongoDB & JWT keys</li>
      <li>Run app locally → <code>npm start</code></li>
      <li>Deployed link hosted on Netlify or Vercel</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

